FBIS4-43087 "drweu113_p_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 GREECE Spokesman Calls U.S. Position on Aegean `Old' Spokesman Calls U.S. Position on Aegean `Old' NC1006151794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 10 Jun 94 NC1006151794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today noted that the problem in the Aegean can be pinpointed to violations by Turkish planes, violation of air-traffic rules, and violations of Greek national airspace. Venizelos said that U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher's position is an old U.S. position, adding: Our country's position, however, depends on national sovereignty and the need to defend the defensive region. Venizelos stressed: Greece always acts defensively.
